text.text: عمل • (ʕimil) (form I, present بعمل‎ (biʕmil), active participle عامل‎ (ʕāmel))
to act (a certain way), to pretend

examples: Synonym: سوّى‎
‏شو بتحبّ نعمل؟‎‎šu bitḥebb niʕmil?What would you like for us to do?
šu bitḥebb niʕmil?
What would you like for us to do?
‏يلّا تعالي، شو بتعملي؟‎‎yalla taʕāli, šu btiʕmili?Come on, what are you doing?
yalla taʕāli, šu btiʕmili?
Come on, what are you doing?
Synonym: سوّى‎
‏عملتلي دور.‎‎ʕimlatli dōr.She made an appointment for me.
ʕimlatli dōr.
She made an appointment for me.
‏رح أعملكم أشياء زاكية.‎‎raḥ ʔaʕmilkom ʔašyāʔ zākye.I'm going to prepare some sweets for you.
raḥ ʔaʕmilkom ʔašyāʔ zākye.
I'm going to prepare some sweets for you.
‏عمل حاله نايم.‎‎ʕimil ḥālo nāyem.He acted like he was asleep.
ʕimil ḥālo nāyem.
He acted like he was asleep.

examples: ‏وَاحِد، اِثْنَان، ثَلَاثَة، أَرْبَعَة، خَمْسَة، سِتَّة، سَبْعَة‎wāḥid, iṯnān, ṯalāṯa, ʔarbaʕa, ḵamsa, sitta, sabʕaone, two, three, four, five, six, seven
wāḥid, iṯnān, ṯalāṯa, ʔarbaʕa, ḵamsa, sitta, sabʕa
one, two, three, four, five, six, seven
Antonym: من‎
‏الختيار راح عالمستشفى.‎‎il-ḵityār rāḥ ʕal-mustašfaThe old man went to the hospital.
il-ḵityār rāḥ ʕal-mustašfa
The old man went to the hospital.
‏إمّي دخلت عالبيت.‎‎ʔimmi daḵlat ʕal-bētMy mother went into the house.
ʔimmi daḵlat ʕal-bēt
My mother went into the house.
‏قدّيش دفعت عليه؟‎‎ʔaddēš dafaʕt ʕalēhHow much did you pay for it?
ʔaddēš dafaʕt ʕalēh
How much did you pay for it?

ḥoṭṭo ʕaṭ-ṭāwle
Put it on the table.

ḵallīna niltʔi ʕala sāʕa sitte
Let's meet at six o'clock.
Synonym: لازم‎
‏قرّرنا نعمل اللي علينا ونتّكل على ربّنا.‎‎ʔarrarna niʕmil illi ʕalēna w nittakil ʕala rabbnaWe resolved to do what we must and trust in God.
ʔarrarna niʕmil illi ʕalēna w nittakil ʕala rabbna
We resolved to do what we must and trust in God.
‏إلي عليك ألف شيكل.‎‎ʔili ʕalēk ʔalf šēkelYou owe me one thousand shekels.
ʔili ʕalēk ʔalf šēkel
You owe me one thousand shekels.
